import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['speed'] = pd.to_numeric(data['speed'], errors='coerce')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='speed', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['speed'].median(), color='red', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['speed'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of wind speed?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['dir'] = data['dir'].astype(int)
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='dir', bins=36, kde=False)
    plt.axvline(data['dir'].median(), color='red', label=f'Median: {data["dir"].median():.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of wind direction?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.copy()
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    sns.countplot(x="dirCat", data=data, palette="Set3")
    plt.title("What is the distribution of wind direction categories?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="white")
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 8))
    sns.kdeplot(data=data, x="longitude", y="latitude", cmap="Reds", shade=True, thresh=0.05, ax=ax)
    ax.set_title("What is the spatial distribution of wind vectors?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
